docs.abstract: Republicans are facing challenges in recruiting Senate candidates, even in states that President Trump won easily in 2016.
docs.snippet: Republicans are facing challenges in recruiting Senate candidates, even in states that President Trump won easily in 2016.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Kevin Cramer, Republican of North Dakota, said on Thursday that he would not challenge the Democratic incumbent senator, Heidi Heitkamp, in this year’s midterm elections. It was just the latest indication of the difficulty Republicans are having recruiting candidates in what had looked to be a highly favorable climate in the wake of President Trump’s inauguration a year ago.

headline.main: Republicans’ ‘Tough Cycle’ Now Spreads to Senate
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Finds Candidates For Senate Are Scarce

docs.abstract: The Trump administration is again asking a judge for more time to return many children to their parents, some of whom have already been deported.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration is again asking a judge for more time to return many children to their parents, some of whom have already been deported.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump administration said Thursday that it had complied with a judge’s order and reunited all of the eligible children under the age of 5 that it had in custody with their migrant parents. But Nazario Jacinto-Carrillo’s desperate voice and haunting questions, repeated over and over on a phone line from Guatemala, made clear that the crisis over child separations remained far from resolved.

headline.main: ‘I Want Her Back’: Some Migrant Families Reunite, but Other Parents Grow Desperate
headline.print_headline: ‘I Want Her Back’: Some Migrant Parents Desperate as Others Reunite

byline.original: By Caitlin Dickerson, Miriam Jordan and Ron Nixon

docs.abstract: The Infowars founder is seeking the dismissal of a bellwether defamation lawsuit this week, as social media platforms take steps to curb him.
docs.snippet: The Infowars founder is seeking the dismissal of a bellwether defamation lawsuit this week, as social media platforms take steps to curb him.
docs.lead_paragraph: AUSTIN, Tex. — In the five years since Noah Pozner was killed at Sandy Hook Elementary School in Newtown, Conn., death threats and online harassment have forced his parents, Veronique De La Rosa and Leonard Pozner, to relocate seven times. They now live in a high-security community hundreds of miles from where their 6-year-old is buried.

headline.main: Alex Jones, Pursued Over Infowars Falsehoods, Faces a Legal Crossroads
headline.print_headline: Judge to Rule on Sandy Hook Family’s Suit Against Infowars Founder

docs.abstract: If President Trump wanted a national security adviser who would match his confrontational approach to the world, then Mr. Bolton fits the bill.
docs.snippet: If President Trump wanted a national security adviser who would match his confrontational approach to the world, then Mr. Bolton fits the bill.
docs.lead_paragraph: John R. Bolton is hardly known for sugarcoating his views. He once derided the United Nations by citing its 38-story headquarters in New York. “If it lost 10 stories,” he said, “it wouldn’t make a bit of difference.”

headline.main: John Bolton, an Undiplomatic Voice for American Might
headline.print_headline: Hawk Among Hawks Eager to Confront Foreign Adversaries

docs.abstract: Representative Patrick Meehan, Republican of Pennsylvania, released this statement in response to an article about a settlement using public funds for misconduct.
docs.snippet: Representative Patrick Meehan, Republican of Pennsylvania, released this statement in response to an article about a settlement using public funds for misconduct.
docs.lead_paragraph: The New York Times received the following statement on Saturday from the office of Representative Patrick Meehan, Republican of Pennsylvania, in response to reporting that Mr. Meehan had used taxpayer funds to settle a case of sexual misconduct with a female staffer in his office.

headline.main: Patrick Meehan’s Response to The Times’s Article on His Settlement for Misconduct

docs.abstract: Senator Heidi Heitkamp, a centrist Democrat in a pitched re-election battle in North Dakota, voted to roll back banking rules. A Koch-backed group is praising her for it.
docs.snippet: Senator Heidi Heitkamp, a centrist Democrat in a pitched re-election battle in North Dakota, voted to roll back banking rules. A Koch-backed group is praising her for it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Heidi Heitkamp, the centrist Democrat from North Dakota who is fighting a pitched battle to save her seat, has gotten a lift from an unlikely source: the conservative billionaire Koch brothers.

headline.main: For Heitkamp, a Lift From an Unlikely Source: The Koch Brothers
headline.print_headline: Democratic Senator’s Newest Allies? The Koch Brothers

docs.abstract: The multimillion-dollar ad campaign comes as Republican lawmakers continue to express dismay over President Trump’s trade moves but insist they are powerless to stop it.
docs.snippet: The multimillion-dollar ad campaign comes as Republican lawmakers continue to express dismay over President Trump’s trade moves but insist they are powerless to stop it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The conservative Koch political network said on Monday that it would begin a multimillion-dollar advertising campaign to promote free trade, sharpening a disagreement with President Trump over tariffs and highlighting a growing rift between conservative donors and the Republican base on trade issues.

headline.main: Conservative Koch Groups Plan Pro-Trade Blitz, as the Issue Splits Republicans
headline.print_headline: Koch Groups Plan Ad Blitz To Push Free Trade Agenda

docs.abstract: Federal judges say that employers cannot legally discriminate against employees transitioning from one sex to the other.
docs.snippet: Federal judges say that employers cannot legally discriminate against employees transitioning from one sex to the other.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Employers are moving to adopt or strengthen policies to prevent bias against transgender people after the latest in a series of court rulings that have extended protections for an increasingly diverse work force.

headline.main: Transgender Workers Gain New Protection Under Court Ruling
headline.print_headline: Transgender Workers  Gain New Protection  In U.S. Court Ruling
